## 1. Kong 502 on `/functions/v1/*` after `dev-start.bat`
**Signature:** 502 on `/functions/v1/*`; kong upstream stale edge_runtime IP.
**Root cause:** Kong upstream cache stale after `functions serve` recreates the container.
**Reference:** `dev-start.ps1` `[8b/10]`; `46cbf4ac`; #617.
## 2. Step 1b red `python.exe` + MCP render failed
**Signature:** stderr success line from gcloud then MCP render exit 1 despite OK auth.
**Root cause:** gcloud writes success to stderr; PS `Stop` mode treats it as terminating (7.3+).
**Reference:** `scripts/render-mcp-config.ps1`; `157ab9a6`.
## 3. `types.ts` polluted with Supabase CLI banners
**Signature:** Post-`-Force`, `types.ts` gains `Connecting to db 5432` / CLI upgrade-banner lines; dirty (`tsc --noEmit` passes).
**Root cause:** Step 6 pipes raw `npx supabase gen types typescript --local` stdout/stderr to disk; `.cursor/hooks/sync-types.ps1` anchors (`^export type` … `^} as const`).
**Workaround:** #620 — `git checkout -- src/integrations/supabase/types.ts`.
## 4. Fleet map markers, no basemap tiles
[`fleet-map.mdc`](./fleet-map.mdc): `useGoogleMapsKey` only with `<MapView>`.
## 5. CSP blocks `data:image/png` on fleet map
**Signature:** `shared-label-worker.js` CSP errors on `data:` URIs.
**Root cause:** Vector labels `fetch(data:)` → `connect-src` needs `data:`.
**Reference:** `vite.config.ts`, `vercel.json`; `b42326b0`.
## 6. `supabase start` WSAEACCES on 543xx
**Signature:** WSAEACCES bind on 543xx; no listener/containers; `netsh excludedportrange` overlaps 54321-54328 (no `*`).
**Root cause:** Ephemeral-range / WinNAT - **not Docker**; AGENTS.md.
**Fix:** `.\scripts\reserve-supabase-ports.ps1` (elevated). Alt: `net stop winnat`; `netsh int ipv4 add excludedportrange protocol=tcp startport=54321 numberofports=8 store=persistent`; `net start winnat`. Verify `54321  54328  *`. Green dev-start before fix claims; AGENTS.md.
